  "text": "The G1 garbage collector's concurrent marking and mixed collection cycle is orchestrated through several key C++ components in openjdk/jdk:\n\n**Cycle Start Trigger:**\nThe concurrent marking cycle is triggered by the G1IHOPControl (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1IHOPControl.hpp/cpp) which implements the Implicit Hoist Ordering Policy to determine when old generation allocation has reached a threshold requiring mark cycle initiation. The G1CollectorState (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1CollectorState.hpp/cpp) tracks the collection state, particularly the in_concurrent_start_gc() flag which indicates when a concurrent start GC is in progress.\n\n**Concurrent Mark Cycle Orchestration:**\nThe G1ConcurrentMarkThread (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMarkThread.hpp/cpp) manages the overall marking cycle phases. It calls concurrent_cycle_start() in G1ConcurrentMark (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMark.hpp/cpp), then progresses through multiple phases: phase_scan_root_regions(), phase_mark_loop() with subphases including mark_from_roots() and preclean(), followed by phase_rebuild_and_scrub() and phase_cleanup().\n\n**SATB Marking Queue Processing:**\nDuring concurrent marking, the Snapshot-At-The-Beginning (SATB) marking queue system ensures correctness. G1SATBMarkQueueSet (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1SATBMarkQueueSet.hpp/cpp) manages thread-local SATB queues (inherited from SATBMarkQueue in src/hotspot/share/gc/shared/satbMarkQueue.hpp/cpp). Each thread's SATB queue is accessed via G1ThreadLocalData (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ThreadLocalData.hpp), which stores references to objects written during marking.\n\n**Marking Task Execution:**\nThe G1CMTask class (defined in src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMark.hpp/cpp) executes the actual marking work. It uses G1CMOopClosure (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1OopClosures.hpp/cpp) to iterate over object references and mark live objects. Tasks are queued in task queues (G1CMTaskQueue/G1CMTaskQueueSet) and executed by multiple worker threads.\n\n**Remembered Set Scanning and Rebuild:**\nAfter marking completes, the G1ConcurrentRebuildAndScrub (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentRebuildAndScrub.hpp/cpp) class handles rebuilding and scrubbing remembered sets. The G1RemSet (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1RemSet.hpp/cpp) manages the remembered set infrastructure with G1RemSetScanState for scan state tracking. Each G1HeapRegion has a G1HeapRegionRemSet (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1HeapRegionRemSet.hpp/cpp) that tracks cross-region references using card tables.\n\n**Mixed Collection Region Selection:**\nAfter marking completes and remark is finished, the G1CollectionSetChooser (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1CollectionSetChooser.hpp/cpp) builds a sorted list of candidate regions for mixed collection. The static build() method processes all regions and calculates GC efficiency metrics. Candidate regions are stored in G1CollectionSetCandidates (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1CollectionSetCandidates.hpp/cpp). The G1YoungCollector (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1YoungCollector.hpp/cpp) then performs evacuation of young and selected old regions during mixed GC pauses. The G1Policy (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1Policy.hpp/cpp) makes decisions on which regions to include based on evacuation predictions and pause time targets.\n\nThe entire cycle is coordinated within G1CollectedHeap (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1CollectedHeap.hpp/cpp) which orchestrates the do_collection_pause_at_safepoint() operations that transition between young-only and mixed collection phases."
}

